      "content": "It’s best to present a balanced view—acknowledge meritocracy as an ideal where individuals advance based on talent and effort but also highlight its limitations as a theory when detached from the context of systemic inequalities. Argue that meritocracy presupposes a level playing field, but in reality, societal structures and historical context have severely limited opportunities for marginalized groups. By focusing on efforts to uphold this narrow view of meritocracy without addressing systemic issues, it can seem idealistic and disconnected from the lived experiences of many. Emphasize that addressing racial inequality through wealth redistribution does not undermine meritocracy; rather, it ensures fair chances for everyone to succeed, strengthening the meritocratic system in a more equitable way.",
